{"build_type":"library","description":"Standard-transport adapter for the Channel-B MCP edge. The MCP host (Claude Code) spawns this as a stdio MCP server: it reads its socket_path from the request, connects to the running kernel Channel-B answer-mcp pathname socket, then delegates to relay-polled-bytes-across-paired-descriptors-perpetually which transparently relays raw bytes both directions between standard input/output and that socket via an event-driven poll loop. The host therefore speaks the standard MCP stdio transport (newline-delimited JSON-RPC over the spawned child stdin/stdout) while the in-world kernel keeps serving through the portal; this adapter is a pure byte relay and parses no MCP. Additive: it adds the missing standard transport edge without touching the existing socket-serving answer-mcp.","module_name":"relay-standard-streams-across-pathname-socket-connection","package_name":"relay-standard-streams-across-pathname-socket-connection","function_definitions":{"relay-standard-streams-across-pathname-socket-connection":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"i2","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"i6","variable_ty